Create EC2:
1. Software Image (AMI) - Amazon Linux 2 Kernel 5.10
2. Virtual server type (instance type) - t2.medium
#############################################################

Install jenkins:
sudo yum update â€“y
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo     https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
sudo yum upgrade
yum install java-17
yum install jenkins
systemctl enable jenkins
systemctl start jenkins
systemctl status jenkins
##############################################################

Install docker:
yum install docker
service start docker
systemctl start docker
systemctl docker status
systemctl status docker
----------------------------
Add a docker user as dockeradmin:
adduser dockeradmin
passwd dockeradmin
----------------------------
To run the user we have to give permission follow below instruction:
run visudo command
Under allow root to runany commands anywhere add:
dockeradmin  ALL=(ALL)  NOPASSWD: ALL
----------------------------
We have to establish the ssh connection and enter this path to establish:
run vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config 
set "PasswordAuthentication yes"
----------------------------
Next we have to give permission for the user:
run usermod -a -G docker dockeradmin
run "service sshd restart"
----------------------------
Go inside docker user and write the docker file vi Dockerfile:
# Pull base image
From tomcat:latest

# Maintainer
MAINTAINER "deep"

# copy war file on to container
COPY ./sampleapp.war /usr/local/tomcat/webapps
##############################################################

Configure Jenkins:
1. Copy the public ip & paste in browse along with the port number to access Jenkins UI.
2. To get the password copy the path from UI "/var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword" and paste it in aws terminal with cat command.
3. Copy and Paste the password to login.
4. Select install suggested plugins.
5. Now we have to give username and  password and email and clickon save and continue. 
6. The dashboard of Jenkins will appear.
7. Next we have to go for manage Jenkins to download plugin.
8. Next we have to install publish over ssh plugin in Jenkins.
9. Next we have to configure maven in global tool configuration in jenkins.
10. 
